{
  "doc_id": "7702",
  "text": "For the first step, we apply a variant of Mask R-CNN [CITATION_1] for joint athlete detection and 2D pose estimation. We modify it to generate higher resolution keypoint estimates and adapt it to the athletics domain with a suitable set of keypoints. For the second step, we model the discrimination of discrete events in a pose sequence as a sequence translation task, where continuous event timing indicators are predicted. The timing indicators encode the temporal distance to the previous and next event in a pose sequence. This continuous encoding of discrete events is used as the learning objective for a temporal sequence CNN, which employs dilated convolutions over time to efficiently process pose sequences of variable length. The final discrete event occurrences can easily be extracted from the estimated timing indicators.",
